rch with real world applications  the William J  Link Professor and chair of biomedical engineering at UC Irvine and its CADMIM director University Cooperative Research Centers program  which fosters long term partnerships among academia  industry and government in various technology sectors  The center has worked with several industry leaders over the last five years  including Procter   Gamble  Beckman Coulter  KWS  Monsanto  QIAGEN  Canon U S  Life Sciences  GSK  Genomics Institute of the Novartis Research Foundation  Douglas Scientific  Amgen Inc  Genentech Inc  Corning Inc  Los Alamos National Laboratories and Air Force Research Labs CADMIM industry partners provide funding for university researchers to develop solutions for specific needs or problems UIC and UC Irvine CADMIM researchers working with GSK  are developing a human liver culture platform using induced pluripotent stem cell technology that can be used to screen thousands of compounds in early drug discovery using a sustainable and genetically diverse source of patient specific cells  this platform can be used to mitigate the risk of drug toxicity to patients in the clinic  as well as develop novel therapeutics against global human liver diseases such as hepatitis B viral infection  non alcoholic fatty liver disease and hepatocellular carcinoma  associate professor of bioengineering at UIC and a lead researcher on the liver project In another project  working with KWS  a German company focused on plant breeding  Other UIC projects have produced point of David Eddington and Jie Xu from the University of Illinois at Chicago and Elliot Hui  Jered Haun  Michelle Khine and Michelle Digman from UC Irvine  are other key researchers in CADMIM  n nContact n nSharon Parmet n t t t t t t t             nsparmet uic edu n n n nCategories n nResearch  n Contact  nSharon Parmet n t t t t t t t             nsparmet uic edu n Sharon Parmet sparmet uic edu Categories  nResearch  Research Topics microfluidic device mic